25 451.598, inclusive, a person that accepts an anatomical gift of an entire body may
26 allow embalming, burial or cremation, and use of remains in a funeral service. If
27 the gift is of a part, the person to which the part passes under NRS 451.571, upon
28 the death of the donor and before embalming, burial or cremation, shall cause the
29 part to be removed without unnecessary mutilation.
30 8. Neither the physician who attends the decedent at death nor the physician
31 who determines the time of the decedent’s death may participate in the procedures
32 for removing or transplanting a part from the decedent.
33 9. A physician or technician may remove a donated part from the body of a
